Test file: src/claim-office.spec.ts
Failing test: "should return 55 G for 2 runes (50 base, no block + 5 fee)"
Expected behavior: Two runes should sum to 50 base (25 each) + 5 fee = 55
Current error: expected 30 to be 55 — implementation only looks at items[0]
Implementation file: src/claim-office.ts

Current implementation:
```typescript
const PROCESSING_FEE = 5;

const BASE_PREMIUMS: Record<string, number> = {
  sword: 100,
  amulet: 60,
  staff: 80,
  potion: 40,
  rune: 25,
  moonstone: 25,
};

export function claimOffice(request: any): any {
  const item = request.steps[0].items[0];
  const basePremium = BASE_PREMIUMS[item.type];
  return [{ premium: basePremium + PROCESSING_FEE }];
}
```

Change the implementation to iterate over ALL items in the step, summing their base premiums, then add the processing fee. This is the minimal change to make both the new test and existing tests pass.

EXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously, proceed to Refactor after completion.

